Purpose
This file defines the orchestration context and the functions that update it over time.

Linear intent
1. Build an `Agent_set` so the system can efficiently remember which agents already ran.
2. Define the `event` record to capture auditable runtime facts with step index, label, detail, and timestamp.
3. Define the main context record with task id, message history, metadata, completed agents, events, and step count.
4. Provide `empty` to create a clean starting context.
5. Provide `add_message` to extend the history when a caller wants to append a message manually.
6. Provide `record_event` to append a generic event with the current step count.
7. Provide `has_completed_agent` so the router can avoid looping back to the same stage incorrectly.
8. Provide `completed_agent_names` so the CLI can print the finished path.
9. Implement `record_outcome` to update history, completed agents, events, and step count after one agent finishes.
10. Implement `record_outcomes` to fold many agent results into the context during parallel execution.
11. Implement `record_parallel_join` to add a dedicated event when a fan-out stage joins back together.
12. Implement `step_budget_exhausted` so the router can stop when the configured maximum number of steps has been reached.

